Django-WordPress
This project is a simple integration of WordPress with Django using the WordPress REST API.

Installation
Clone the repository to your local machine.
Create a virtual environment for the project and activate it.
Install the dependencies by running pip install -r requirements.txt.
Configure the database in the settings.py file.
Run the migrations by running python manage.py migrate.
Start the development server by running python manage.py runserver.
Usage
Once the server is running, you can access the Django admin panel at http://localhost:8000/admin/ and the WordPress site at http://localhost:8000/wordpress/.

Features
Integrates WordPress with Django using the WordPress REST API.
Allows for easy management of WordPress content through the Django admin panel.
Provides a seamless user experience for visitors to the WordPress site.
